<paragraph blockId="10.[264,1323,353,574]" pageId="10" pageNumber="39">
Remarks—Found primarily on 
<taxonomicName box="[682,831,428,453]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Mus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="10" pageNumber="39" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="musculus">
<emphasis box="[682,831,428,453]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="39">M. musculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it has been recorded only in the states of Distrito Federal, 
<collectingCountry box="[466,555,468,494]" name="Mexico" pageId="10" pageNumber="39">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and Guanajuato. This species has been implicated as a vector of murine typhus. 
<taxonomicName box="[457,679,508,533]" class="Insecta" family="Leptopsyllidae" genus="Leptopsylla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonaptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="segnis">
<emphasis box="[457,679,508,533]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="39">Leptopsylla segnis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is undoubtedly more widely spread in 
<collectingCountry box="[1170,1260,508,534]" name="Mexico" pageId="10" pageNumber="39">Mexico</collectingCountry>
than indicated by available records; there is a need for future surveillance.
</paragraph>
